<head>DIRECTION</head>
    <list type="altnames">
<item>DIMENSION</item>
    </list>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">方向</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>RELATION to OTHER PLACES.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The general term for direction as defining a part of space is fāng 方.</p>
<p>2. Xiāng 鄉 refers to a direction as seen from a subject.</p>
<p>3. Dōng 東 "east", nán 南 "south", xī 西 "west", běi 北 are the major directions.</p>
<p>4. Yáng 陽 refers to the area north of a river and south of a mountain.</p>
<p>5. Yīn 陰 refers to the area south of a river and north of a mountain.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>方向</p>
